The paper deals with qualitative reasoning under uncertainty, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of possibility theory and Dempster-Shafer evidence theory also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also involves the analysis of directed graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and graph theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of different formalisms, which could be seen as a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
